{"id":"d=origam-topic-3986//p=21827fe0f6ca426d86ddf504540a0f16","tags":{"__document_id":["origam-topic-3986"],"__file_type":["text/plain"],"__file_id":["98a08942588141f19397e67974f2b624"],"__file_part":["9923793607904cdca3f7693ee67d7901"],"__part_n":["1"],"__sect_n":["0"],"source":["origam-community"],"topicId":["3986"],"categoryId":["61"],"url":["https://community.origam.com/t/how-to-setup-the-client-application/3986"],"title":["How to setup the client application"],"imagesFound":["12"],"imagesDescribed":["12"],"imageUrl":["https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/f/f2aea50249a68e5c5c0015494d72a8cf341a80d0.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/6/6f1d32f9c6b7f3ad7942dd02e45735338afe4052.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/9d46654a21ab9c83218298b52384441c8144781d.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2df3e40fa53d239c0c17a8bd9754cde016165657.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/5ab0a264457efa6ebc2d0c92b02810fd12ae77ec.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/5/511c1ee021229f53600e1ebb2daa5fe7e5edeb0d.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/d/d6a188d295b7b0d9922857099fec68589aeb8be5.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/4/4db6549d4e773494c209e56914bceee3727711d8.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/ebc55c277fcb00ed8330896fe8d3365e8722dea1.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/b/b4203ab0b6f949d5411d37585de0ae889524184f.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/e/e5d36ee8bf5b91cbde8c9b2e6c525e60ed147e08.png","https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/1/18958f693db4fa700988d52922938c00db5b8d1f.jpeg"]},"payload":{"url":"","schema":"20231218A","file":"content.txt","text":"9c6b7f3ad7942dd02e45735338afe4052.png]\nDescription: The image depicts a configuration panel labeled \u0022IdentityGuiConfig,\u0022 which focuses on the setting for allowing password resets. It contains a description of the \u0022AllowPasswordReset\u0022 option, indicating it accepts boolean values of true or false. The text explains that setting this option to true enables users to reset their passwords independently, whereas setting it to false removes the password reset option from the login screen.\n\n\n  \n This parameter will have the following record in the .env file: \n  IdentityGuiConfig__AllowPasswordReset=true  \n This setting, for example, will allow the users to reset their password and provide a link for it on the login screen. \n   OrigamSettings.config \n The format here is  OrigamSettings__parameter=value . So it is actually the same format as in the AppSettings.json file, but the name of the element here is always \u201COrigamSettings\u201D. \n Example from  documentation : \n \n  Configuration  \n HelpUrl  \nIf specified the web application user menu contains menu item  Help  leading to the specified url. The default value is  http://origam.com/doc . \n \n This parameter will have the following record in the .env file: \n  OrigamSettings__HelpUrl=http://origam.com/documentation . \n In addition to that there is also database connection configuration: \n  OrigamSettings__DataConnectionString=Data Source=host.docker.internal,1433;Initial Catalog=MyApplication;Integrated Security=False;User ID=MyUsername;Password=MyPassword;Pooling=True;Encrypt=False\n  \n Anytime you change the Docker .env file you need to restart it in order that your changes take effect. \n   Directory mapping \n In some cases, beside changing the .env file you will also need to change the Docker command (.cmd) file as well. This file is located in the same directory as the .env file and we will use it to map local and server directories. \n For example this line in the .cmd file: \n -v \u0022c:\\OrigamProjects\\MyApplication\\customAssets\u0022:/home/origam/projectData/customAssets  \nmeans that the folder  c:\\OrigamProjects\\MyApplication\\customAssets  will mirror in the server folder  /home/origam/projectData/customAssets . \n After changing the .cmd file you need to delete the entire Docker container and create it again running the cmd file. Only then the changes will take effect. More on that  here . \n To verify that everything works fine you can check your Docker container environment variables directly in Docker: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/9/9d46654a21ab9c83218298b52384441c8144781d.png]\nDescription: The image displays a user interface for inspecting a container identified as \u0022myapp,\u0022 with ID \u0022757445a0dc61.\u0022 The \u0022Env\u0022 section lists various environment variables configured for the container. Visible UI text includes \u0022OriginSettings_SetOnStart=true,\u0022 \u0022OriginSettings_SchemaExtensionGuid=249dde603-c28d-4a37-97c5-b3577e4dacd0,\u0022 \u0022OriginSettings_DbHost=host.docker.internal,\u0022 \u0022OriginSettings_DbPort=1337,\u0022 \u0022OriginSettings_DbUsername=3a,\u0022 \u0022OriginSettings_DbPassword=MyDbPassword,\u0022 \u0022OriginSettings_HelpUrl=http://origin.com/documentation,\u0022 \u0022IdentityGuiConfig_AllowPasswordReset=true,\u0022 \u0022DatabaseName=myapp,\u0022 \u0022DatabaseType=msql,\u0022 \u0022ExternalDomain_Setting=localhost,\u0022 and \u0022TZ=Europe/Prague.\u0022 The purpose of this interface is to manage environment variables for the container setup related to the application configuration.\n\n\n  \n Finally you can see the effect in the client application, for example here: \n  \n\n\n[Image: https://community.origam.com/uploads/default/original/2X/2/2df3e40fa53d239c0c17a8bd9754cde016165657.png]\nDescription: The image features a login interface designed for user authentication, displaying fields for \u0027Username\u0027 and \u0027Password.\u0027 The \u0027Username\u0027 field is located at the top, followed by the \u0027Password\u0027 field immediately below it. Below these input fields, there are two buttons: a blue \u0027Log In\u0027 button and a blue \u0027Cancel\u0027 button. Additionally, there is a prompt at the bottom in a red box stating, \u0022Click here to reset your password.\u0022 The overall purpose of this interface is to allow users to log into a system or application while providing an option to reset their password if needed.\n\n\n","vector_provider":"AI.Ollama.OllamaTextEmbeddingGenerator","vector_generator":"__","last_update":"2026-05-01T23:53:59"},"vector":[-0.015830902,-0.002422979,-0.070325285,-0.048484717,-0.04365074,-0.040574532,0.03695626,-0.006917291,0.0023041721,0.005689797,-0.01165647,0.0026821804,-0.0096812975,-0.0027271912,0.029600512,-0.04285039,0.0064984583,0.0022393006,0.03215274,0.021452472,-0.019713134,-0.022143232,0.040582094,-0.031055732,0.037737776,0.04438015,-0.01117177,-0.040260132,0.00086643314,0.024712188,-0.00593064,-0.05928761,-0.027584935,-0.0072488,0.028425325,0.016587613,0.035854958,-0.005664926,-0.038617212,0.025975661,0.008133732,-0.027972613,-0.014403188,0.028548704,0.012771819,-0.047382478,0.010053203,0.0027973098,0.003934894,-0.053354587,-0.021933075,-0.032720357,0.053616714,-0.055057403,-0.0047101546,0.05775423,-0.03406135,0.0059009264,-0.049343005,-0.029954897,0.015812622,-0.023782644,-0.025783714,-0.033091106,-0.02285316,0.0030075565,-0.028143287,0.026792394,-0.02562688,-0.028067747,0.022452664,0.02285029,-0.056095745,-0.030130258,-0.07625717,0.017175917,0.008698418,0.02047006,-0.025650697,-0.009680884,-0.008563342,0.012431082,0.008931452,0.004403083,0.014656121,0.01800609,-0.034624748,0.057852056,0.043454606,0.011899596,-0.03400058,-0.024373356,0.07996332,-0.044784725,-0.018469429,0.0075102826,-0.002160034,-0.042480677,0.0033922405,0.020734139,-0.008961057,-0.013635219,-0.014998568,-0.0077307993,-0.009099908,0.01561732,0.039938603,-0.008435732,-0.024723534,-0.035695598,-0.011147793,0.026014602,0.033274606,-0.028800013,-0.0045665223,-0.0011099229,-0.006064